title gitleaks: recommended, not required
supersedes 7c593f3a576affdafa96a58dc2e45b19cdb055cd
edge explains commit:ea10985161f3053d17355bd29e32cc448c7e76f8

gitleaks is a strongly recommended tool for secret scanning but not a strict
dependency. When gitleaks is installed:

1. mycelium.sh note scans content before writing (gitleaks dir on tmpfile)
2. pre-commit hook scans staged changes (gitleaks git --staged)
3. pre-push hook scans all refs including notes (gitleaks git, --all is default)

When gitleaks is absent, all three layers silently skip — mycelium works
normally without it. The test suite (test-gitleaks.sh) also SKIPs gracefully.

Key finding during implementation: gitleaks v8.30 runs git log -p --all by
default, which includes refs/notes/*. No special config needed to scan notes.
Also: git notes remove does NOT erase history — the add commit stays in the
notes ref log. A secret once written to a note is permanent in --all history.
Use .gitleaksignore or baseline for known false positives.
